{"type": "function", "function": {"name": "save_prompt_to_hub", "description": "Save a new prompt to the Prompt Hub with optional tools/function calling configuration.

    This tool saves a new prompt in the hub with messages and optional tool definitions.
    It writes a confirmation message to the conversation upon success.

    When the prompt was loaded from the hub (instances[].loadedPrompt has promptId), this tool automatically saves as a new version. Otherwise it creates a new prompt.

    NAMING CONSTRAINTS: Max length 200 chars. Names must be unique per space (case-sensitive).

    IMPORTANT: When saving a prompt from the playground, check input_context.prompt_playground_state.instances
    to find the instance (A, B, or C) that contains the prompt you want to save.

    Use this to save prompts created or optimized during the session.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"name": {"description": "Short, concise name for the prompt (max 200 chars, must be unique in the space). Examples: 'Travel Planner', 'Code Review', 'Email Draft'", "type": "string"}, "messages_json": {"description": "JSON array of messages in the format: [{"role": "system|user|assistant", "content": "..."}].
        Example: '[{"role": "system", "content": "You are a helpful assistant"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]'", "type": "string"}, "instance_letter": {"default": "A", "description": "Which playground instance letter (A, B, or C) this prompt is from.
